
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class Person {
  +personID: String
  +phone: String
  +keywords: List<String>
  +institutionCode: String
}

class Institution {
  +institutionCode: String
  +name: String
  +address: String
}

class Article {
  +doi: String
  +title: String
  +authors: List<Person>
  +authorPositions: List<Integer>
  +type: String
}

class PeerReviewedArticle extends Article {
  +citationCount: Integer
  +reviewers: List<Person>
}

class TechnicalReport extends Article {
  +publisher: Institution
}

class Publisher {
  +name: String
  +journals: List<Journal>
}

class Journal {
  +name: String
  +impactFactor: Double
  +publisher: Publisher
}

' Associations
Person --|> Institution : worksFor
Article --|> Person : authoredBy
Article --|> Person : reviewedBy
PeerReviewedArticle --|> Article
TechnicalReport --|> Article
Article --|> Publisher : publishedIn (for PeerReviewedArticle)
Publisher --|> Journal
Institution --|> Journal : publishes (for TechnicalReport)

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Relationships:

- **`Person`** is associated with an **`Institution`** (works for).
- A **`Person`** can be both an **author** and a **reviewer** of articles.
- An **`Article`** has multiple **authors**, each with an **author position**.
- **`Article`** is extended into two types:
  - **`PeerReviewedArticle`** includes **citation count** and **reviewers**.
  - **`TechnicalReport`** is always published by a single **`Institution`**.
- **`Publisher`** publishes **`Journals`**, which have an **impact factor**.
- Only **`PeerReviewedArticle`** can be published in a **`Journal`**.
- **`Journal`** is associated with a **`Publisher`**.

